<div class="control-group">
  <label class="control-label"><input type="checkbox" id="dateShiftCheckbox"></label>
  <div class="controls controlMargin">
     {{#t "checkbox_label"}}Adjust events and due dates{{/t}}
  </div>
</div>

<div class="dateShiftContent control-group" style="display:none">
  <label class="control-label">Future course date range</label>
  <div class="controls">
    <div class="pull-left"> from <input type="text" id="oldStartDate"></div>
    <div class="pull-left">&nbsp;to <input type="text" id="oldEndDate"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="dateShiftContent control-group" style="display:none">
  <label class="control-label">This course date range</label>
  <div class="controls">
    <div class="pull-left"> from <input type="text" id="newStartDate"></div>
    <div class="pull-left">&nbsp;to <input type="text" id="newEndDate"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="dateShiftContent control-group" style="display:none">
  <div class="controls">
    <p>You can also explicitly define day substitutions to adjust for changing class schedules (i.e. move everything that was on Mondays to now happen on Tuesdays)</p>
    <a href="#" id='addDaySubstitution' class="add_substitution_link add">Define a day substitution</a>
    <div id="daySubstitution"></div>
  </div>
</div>
